President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. James Byrne of Virginia is nominated to be the Deputy Secretary of Veterans Affairs. He currently serves as the General Counsel, Performing the Duties of the Deputy Secretary of the Department of Veterans Affairs. Byrne has extensive experience in the public sector, including serving as an executive with Lockheed Martin Corporation and in career Senior Executive Service positions. He earned his J.D. from Stetson University College of Law and is a Distinguished Graduate of the United States Naval Academy.

Nazak Nikakhtar of Maryland is nominated to be the Under Secretary of Commerce for Industry & Security. She currently serves as the Assistant Secretary of Commerce (Industry and Analysis), where she is the Department's primary liaison with United States industry and trade associations. Nikakhtar has previously worked as a partner at the international trade law firm of Cassidy Levy Kent, LLP and as an adjunct professor at Georgetown University Law Center. She received her J.D. and Master of Economics degrees from Syracuse University.

Jonathan R. Cohen of California is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Arab Republic of Egypt. Cohen is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Acting United States Representative to the United Nations and Acting United States Representative to the United Nations Security Council. He has held various other diplomatic positions, including Deputy United States Representative and Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for European and Eurasian Affairs. Cohen earned his A.B. at Princeton University and has received several awards for his service. He speaks French, Swedish, and Italian.